WebGuard is an advanced Web Application Firewall (WAF) and Behavioral Analysis
Engine for OPNsense that provides comprehensive protection against sophisticated
web attacks and insider threats through machine learning-based anomaly detection.

Key features include:
- Protection against SQL injection, XSS, CSRF, and other OWASP Top 10 threats
- ModSecurity-compatible custom rule engine
- Real-time request inspection and file upload protection
- Behavioral profiling and anomaly detection
- Beaconing and data exfiltration pattern detection
- Detection of covert channels (DNS, HTTP, ICMP tunneling)
- Zero Trust model with learning and protection modes
- Geographic IP blocking with GeoIP database integration
- Honeypot redirection, progressive blocking, and tarpits
- Real-time threat feed, SIEM integration, and webhook notifications
- Forensics and audit trail capabilities
- Multi-mode deployment: Learning, Detection, Protection, Zero Trust
- Real-time dashboard with interactive threat visualization
- Scalable performance with horizontal deployment support

Installation requirements:
- OPNsense 24.1 or later
- Python 3.9+ and required modules
- 256MB RAM minimum (512MB recommended)
- 100MB disk space for logs and data

Optional dependencies:
- Scapy for deep packet inspection
- NumPy for machine learning analysis
- PSUtil for resource usage monitoring
- GeoIP database for geographic features

